              width="450"
              height="450"
              loading="lazy"
              class="rounded-lg"
            />
            <figcaption class="text-center text-sm text-gray-500 mt-2">Alfa Laval MOPX207 Used Oil Centrifuge</figcaption>
          </figure>
          <div class="flex-1">
            <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-[#1B3A5C] mb-3">Key Operational Highlights</h3>
            <ul class="space-y-2 text-[#2D2D2D] text-sm">
              <li class="flex gap-2"><span class="text-[#E8A317]">&#x2713;</span> Continuous three-phase separation (oil / water / solids)</li>
              <li class="flex gap-2"><span class="text-[#E8A317]">&#x2713;</span> Self-cleaning bowl — automatic sludge ejection without stopping</li>
              <li class="flex gap-2"><span class="text-[#E8A317]">&#x2713;</span> Small enough for manual service — no lifting equipment needed</li>
              <li class="flex gap-2"><span class="text-[#E8A317]">&#x2713;</span> 316L duplex stainless steel bowl construction</li>
              <li class="flex gap-2"><span class="text-[#E8A317]">&#x2713;</span> Available in standard and explosion-proof (Class 1 Div 2) configurations</li>
              <li class="flex gap-2"><span class="text-[#E8A317]">&#x2713;</span> Processes diesel, lube oil, waste oil, biodiesel, and more</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- MOPX Applications -->
      <div id="applications-mopx" class="bg-white rounded-xl border border-gray-100 shadow-sm p-6 md:p-8 mb-8">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-[#1B3A5C] mb-4">Alfa Laval MOPX-207 — Applications</h2>
        <p class="text-[#2D2D2D] mb-4">
          The MOPX-207 finds a variety of applications in fuel and lubrication purification applications. Some of the popular applications are:
        </p>

        <div class="flex flex-col md:flex-row gap-6 items-start">
          <ul class="grid grid-cols-1 gap-2 flex-1 text-sm text-[#2D2D2D]">
            <li><a href="/diesel-fuel-purifier/" class="flex items-center gap-2 text-[#1B3A5C] hover:text-[#E8A317] p-2 rounded hover:bg-gray-50"><span class="text-[#E8A317]">&#x279C;</span> Diesel Fuel</a></li>
            <li><a href="/waste-oil-centrifuge/" class="flex items-center gap-2 text-[#1B3A5C] hover:text-[#E8A317] p-2 rounded hover:bg-gray-50"><span class="text-[#E8A317]">&#x279C;</span> Waste Oil</a></li>
            <li><a href="/black-diesel-centrifuge/" class="flex items-center gap-2 text-[#1B3A5C] hover:text-[#E8A317] p-2 rounded hover:bg-gray-50"><span class="text-[#E8A317]">&#x279C;</span> Black Diesel</a></li>
            <li><a href="/wvo-centrifuge-separator/" class="flex items-center gap-2 text-[#1B3A5C] hover:text-[#E8A317] p-2 rounded hover:bg-gray-50"><span class="text-[#E8A317]">&#x279C;</span> WVO or Yellow Grease</a></li>
            <li><a href="/biodiesel-centrifuge/" class="flex items-center gap-2 text-[#1B3A5C] hover:text-[#E8A317] p-2 rounded hover:bg-gray-50"><span class="text-[#E8A317]">&#x279C;</span> Biodiesel Glycerol</a></li>
            <li><a href="/fuel-oil-centrifuge/" class="flex items-center gap-2 text-[#1B3A5C] hover:text-[#E8A317] p-2 rounded hover:bg-gray-50"><span class="text-[#E8A317]">&#x279C;</span> Heavy Fuel Oil</a></li>
            <li><a href="/machine-coolant-centrifuge/" class="flex items-center gap-2 text-[#1B3A5C] hover:text-[#E8A317] p-2 rounded hover:bg-gray-50"><span class="text-[#E8A317]">&#x279C;</span> Machining Coolant</a></li>
            <li><a href="/quench-oil-centrifuge/" class="flex items-center gap-2 text-[#1B3A5C] hover:text-[#E8A317] p-2 rounded hover:bg-gray-50"><span class="text-[#E8A317]">&#x279C;</span> Quenching Oil</a></li>
            <li><a href="/crude-oil-centrifuge/" class="flex items-center gap-2 text-[#1B3A5C] hover:text-[#E8A317] p-2 rounded hover:bg-gray-50"><span class="text-[#E8A317]">&#x279C;</span> Light Crude Oil</a></li>
          </ul>
          <figure class="flex-shrink-0">
            <img
              src="/images/alfa-laval-mopx-207-centrifuge/Alfa-Laval-Explosion-Proof-Centrifuge-600.jpg"
              alt="Alfa Laval MAPX-207 Explosion-Proof Centrifuge — Class 1 Div 2 configuration for hazardous environments"
              width="360"
              height="450"
              loading="lazy"
              class="rounded-lg"
            />
            <figcaption class="text-center text-sm text-gray-500 mt-2">Alfa Laval MAPX-207 — Explosion-Proof Centrifuge</figcaption>
          </figure>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- MOPX Specifications -->
      <div id="specifications-mopx" class="bg-white rounded-xl border border-gray-100 shadow-sm p-6 md:p-8 mb-8">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-[#1B3A5C] mb-4">Alfa Laval MOPX 207 — Specifications</h2>
        <div class="overflow-x-auto">
          <table class="w-full text-sm text-[#2D2D2D] border-collapse">
            <thead>
              <tr class="bg-[#1B3A5C] text-white">
                <th class="px-4 py-3 text-left font-semibold w-1/2">Parameter</th>
                <th class="px-4 py-3 text-left font-semibold">Value</th>
              </tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody>
              <tr class="border-b border-gray-100 hover:bg-gray-50">
                <td class="px-4 py-3 font-semibold">Centrifuge Model</td>
                <td class="px-4 py-3 font-mono">Alfa Laval MOPX 207 TGT</td>
              </tr>
              <tr class="border-b border-gray-100 hover:bg-gray-50">
                <td class="px-4 py-3 font-semibold">Capacity — Diesel</td>
                <td class="px-4 py-3 font-mono">28 GPM on 13 cSt Diesel Fuel</td>
              </tr>
              <tr class="border-b border-gray-100 hover:bg-gray-50">
                <td class="px-4 py-3 font-semibold">Capacity — Turbine Lube Oil</td>
                <td class="px-4 py-3 font-mono">22 GPM</td>
              </tr>
              <tr class="border-b border-gray-100 hover:bg-gray-50">
                <td class="px-4 py-3 font-semibold">Capacity — Hydraulic Oil</td>
                <td class="px-4 py-3 font-mono">20 GPM</td>
              </tr>
              <tr class="border-b border-gray-100 hover:bg-gray-50">
                <td class="px-4 py-3 font-semibold">Sludge Space</td>
                <td class="px-4 py-3 font-mono">1.00 Gallons</td>
              </tr>
              <tr class="border-b border-gray-100 hover:bg-gray-50">
                <td class="px-4 py-3 font-semibold">Bowl Speed</td>
                <td class="px-4 py-3 font-mono">6,325 RPM</td>
              </tr>
              <tr class="border-b border-gray-100 hover:bg-gray-50">
                <td class="px-4 py-3 font-semibold">Net Weight</td>
                <td class="px-4 py-3 font-mono">1,800 Lbs.</td>
              </tr>
              <tr class="border-b border-gray-100 hover:bg-gray-50">
                <td class="px-4 py-3 font-semibold">Dimensions</td>
                <td class="px-4 py-3 font-mono">30" x 38" x 43" (Bare Centrifuge)</td>
              </tr>
              <tr class="border-b border-gray-100 hover:bg-gray-50">
                <td class="px-4 py-3 font-semibold">Motor Power</td>
                <td class="px-4 py-3 font-mono">7.5 HP</td>
              </tr>
              <tr class="hover:bg-gray-50">
                <td class="px-4 py-3 font-semibold">Voltages</td>
                <td class="px-4 py-3 font-mono">230 / 460 V; 3-Phase</td>
              </tr>
            </tbody>
          </table>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Material of Construction -->
      <div id="material" class="bg-white rounded-xl border border-gray-100 shadow-sm p-6 md:p-8 mb-8">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-[#1B3A5C] mb-4">Material of Construction</h2>
        <p class="text-[#2D2D2D] mb-4">
          The Alfa Laval MOPX 207 is designed for mineral oil and fuel separation applications. Therefore, the material used in its construction is well suited for such uses. The following table lists the various components of the centrifuge and the material it is made of.
        </p>
        <div class="overflow-x-auto">
          <table class="w-full text-sm text-[#2D2D2D] border-collapse">
            <thead>
              <tr class="bg-[#1B3A5C] text-white">
                <th class="px-4 py-3 text-left font-semibold w-1/2">Component</th>
                <th class="px-4 py-3 text-left font-semibold">Material</th>
              </tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody>
              <tr class="border-b border-gray-100 hover:bg-gray-50">
                <td class="px-4 py-3">Bowl Body &amp; Bowl Hood</td>
                <td class="px-4 py-3 font-mono">316L Duplex Stainless Steel</td>
              </tr>
              <tr class="border-b border-gray-100 hover:bg-gray-50">
                <td class="px-4 py-3">Disc Stack</td>
                <td class="px-4 py-3 font-mono">316L Duplex Stainless Steel</td>
              </tr>
              <tr class="border-b border-gray-100 hover:bg-gray-50">
                <td class="px-4 py-3">Distributor or Disc Carrier</td>
                <td class="px-4 py-3 font-mono">Marine Grade Bronze or 316 Stainless Steel (Special Order)</td>
              </tr>
              <tr class="border-b border-gray-100 hover:bg-gray-50">
                <td class="px-4 py-3">Top Disc</td>
                <td class="px-4 py-3 font-mono">Marine Grade Bronze or 316 Stainless Steel (Special Order)</td>
              </tr>
              <tr class="border-b border-gray-100 hover:bg-gray-50">
                <td class="px-4 py-3">Top Covers (Collecting)</td>
                <td class="px-4 py-3 font-mono">Silium (Aluminum Alloy)</td>
              </tr>
              <tr class="hover:bg-gray-50">
                <td class="px-4 py-3">Frame</td>
                <td class="px-4 py-3 font-mono">Nodular Cast Iron</td>
              </tr>
            </tbody>
          </table>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- FAQ Banner -->
      <div class="bg-[#1B3A5C] text-white rounded-xl p-6 mb-8 text-center">
        <p class="text-sm">
          If you have simple, routine questions: We have condensed our 40+ years of disc-stack centrifuge experience into
          <a href="/disc-stack-centrifuge-faq/" class="underline font-bold hover:text-[#E8A317]">101 Frequently Asked Questions about Disc Stack Centrifuges!</a>
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- WHPX 407 Section -->
      <div id="whpx-407" class="bg-white rounded-xl border border-gray-100 shadow-sm p-6 md:p-8 mb-8">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-[#1B3A5C] mb-4">Alfa Laval WHPX 407 — Partial-Discharge Disc-Stack Centrifuge</h2>
        <p class="text-[#2D2D2D] leading-relaxed mb-4">
          The Alfa Laval WHPX 407 Centrifuge is a self-cleaning disc-stack centrifuge designed for the three-phase separation of fuel oils, such as <a href="/fuel-oil-centrifuge/" class="text-[#E8A317] hover:underline">light fuel oil</a> (LFO).
        </p>
        <p class="text-[#2D2D2D] leading-relaxed mb-4">
          With a <strong>10 HP Motor</strong>, the WHPX 407 centrifuge has a bowl RPM of <strong>7,125</strong> and can process <strong>25 GPM of ISO 180 cSt Light Fuel Oil</strong>.
        </p>
        <p class="text-[#2D2D2D] leading-relaxed mb-6">
          Also, the WHPX-407 is a <strong>partial-discharge centrifuge</strong>. This means that this centrifuge is capable of discharging only the accumulated sludge and minimizing <a href="/centrifuge-product-loss-during-discharge/" class="text-[#E8A317] hover:underline">fluid loss</a>.
        </p>

        <figure class="mb-6">
          <img
            src="/images/alfa-laval-mopx-207-centrifuge/Alfa-Laval-WHPX510-DAF.jpg"
            alt="Alfa Laval WHPX 407 Centrifuge System with 60 kW Electric heater for light fuel oil separation"
            width="450"
            height="450"
            loading="lazy"
            class="rounded-lg mx-auto"
          />
          <figcaption class="text-center text-sm text-gray-500 mt-2">Alfa Laval WHPX 407 Centrifuge System with 60 kW Electric heater</figcaption>
